Start the S3-compatible GrainFS storage server.

You can configure multi-root storage directories (Multi-Drive) to enable disk-level
resilience and Erasure Coding (EC) even on a single node. 

To specify multiple data directories, pass a comma-separated list of paths to the 
--data (-d) flag. It is highly recommended to also specify a fast SSD path via the
--meta-dir flag to keep the BadgerDB metadata separate from payload shards.

Examples:
  # Single-node mode with 3 data drives (automatically configures 2+1 EC):
  grainfs serve -d /mnt/hdd1,/mnt/hdd2,/mnt/hdd3 --meta-dir /mnt/ssd-meta

  # Default single-drive mode (1+0 Solo):
  grainfs serve -d ./data

Usage:
  grainfs serve [flags]

Flags:
      --9p-bind string                                      9P2000.L bind address; set 0.0.0.0 only on trusted networks (default "127.0.0.1")
      --9p-port int                                         9P2000.L server port (0 = disabled); unauthenticated, use firewall
      --admin-group string                                  OS group name for admin socket chown (default: caller's primary group)
      --admin-socket string                                 admin Unix socket path (default <data>/admin.sock)
      --append-size-cap-bytes int                           Per-object total size cap for AppendObject in bytes (default 5 TiB, S3 PutObject parity). (default 5497558138880)
      --audit-commit-interval duration                      how often the audit committer flushes the ring buffer to Iceberg (default 1m0s)
      --audit-iceberg                                       enable audit log lake: S3 ops → Iceberg table on grainfs-audit bucket (default true)
      --badger-gc-disable                                   disable BadgerDB vlog GC ticker (debug only)
      --badger-gc-fail-threshold int32                      consecutive RunValueLogGC failures before incident (default 3)
      --badger-gc-interval duration                         BadgerDB vlog GC ticker cadence (default 5m0s)
      --block-cache-size int                                volume block cache capacity in bytes (0 disables) (default 67108864)
      --cluster-append-forward-buffer-max-per-request int   Max bytes any single AppendObject forward request may reserve (default 64 MiB). (default 67108864)
      --cluster-append-forward-buffer-total-bytes int       Total byte budget for AppendObject forward-body reservation pool (default 512 MiB). (default 536870912)
      --cluster-key string                                  Pre-shared key for cluster peer authentication
  -d, --data string                                         data directory (comma-separated for multi-root) (default "./data")
      --datagroup-refresh-interval duration                 how often to scan for new DataGroups and start reshard managers (0 = only scan at startup) (default 1m0s)
      --degraded-check-interval duration                    EC degraded-mode liveness check interval (default 30s)
      --encryption-key-file string                          path to 32-byte encryption key file (auto-generated only for solo bootstrap if omitted)
      --fd-classification-cap int                           max open file descriptors to classify by category per sample (default 512)
      --fd-critical-threshold float                         FD used fraction (0-1) at which a critical incident fires (default 0.9)
      --fd-eta-window duration                              positive-trend ETA window for predictive FD warnings (default 30m0s)
      --fd-recovery-window duration                         stable below-threshold window before resolving FD incidents (default 1m0s)
      --fd-warn-threshold float                             FD used fraction (0-1) at which a warning incident fires (default 0.8)
      --fd-watch-enabled                                    enable predictive file descriptor exhaustion warnings (default true)
      --fd-watch-interval duration                          how often to sample process file descriptor usage (default 10s)
      --goroutine-critical int                              goroutine count that triggers critical-level alert (default 20000)
      --goroutine-eta-window duration                       ETA projection window for predictive goroutine warnings (default 30m0s)
      --goroutine-poll-interval duration                    polling interval for goroutine count sampling (default 30s)
      --goroutine-recovery-window duration                  minimum time below warn threshold before transitioning to ok (default 1m0s)
      --goroutine-warn int                                  goroutine count that triggers warn-level alert (transition-only firing) (default 5000)
      --goroutine-watch-enabled                             enable predictive goroutine count warnings (default true)
      --heal-receipt-enabled                                enable HealReceipt audit API (default true)
      --heal-receipt-gossip-interval duration               how often this node gossips its recent receipt IDs to peers (default 5s)
      --heal-receipt-psk string                             PSK for HealReceipt HMAC-SHA256 signing (defaults to --cluster-key in cluster mode)
      --heal-receipt-retention duration                     HealReceipt retention window (older entries are GC'd) (default 720h0m0s)
      --heal-receipt-window int                             rolling window size — how many recent receipt IDs to gossip per tick (default 50)
  -h, --help                                                help for serve
      --join-listen-addr string                             Zero-CA QUIC join-listener bind address (leader serves the invite handler); empty derives an ephemeral port on the raft-addr host
      --lifecycle-interval duration                         lifecycle rule evaluation interval (0 to disable) (default 1h0m0s)
      --measure-read-amp                                    enable read-amplification simulator (informs Unified Buffer Cache decision)
      --meta-dir string                                     dedicated fast metadata storage directory (defaults to first path in --data)
      --nbd-port int                                        NBD server port (0 = disabled). Client-side nbd-client still requires Linux. (default 10809)
      --nfs-write-buffer-dir string                         directory for NFS write coalescing buffer files (empty = derive from --data)
      --nfs-write-buffer-idle duration                      idle timeout before write buffer auto-flushes (0 = disable buffering) (default 30s)
      --nfs4-port int                                       NFSv4 server port (0 = disabled); binds 0.0.0.0 — use firewall or set 0 when exposing public interfaces (default 2049)
      --node-id string                                      unique node ID (auto-generated if omitted)
      --otel-endpoint string                                OTLP HTTP endpoint for trace export (empty disables OTel, e.g. localhost:4318)
      --otel-sample-rate float                              head-based OTel trace sample rate [0.0, 1.0] (default 1%) (default 0.01)
      --pack-threshold int                                  pack objects below this size into blob files (0 = disabled, e.g. 65537) (default 65537)
  -p, --port int                                            listen port (default 9000)
      --pprof-port int                                      expose net/http/pprof on this port (0 = disabled, for profiling e2e/load tests)
      --public-url grainfs dashboard                        public dashboard base URL (e.g. https://node1:9000); defaults to localhost in grainfs dashboard output
      --quic-mux-flush duration                             heartbeat coalescing flush window for multiplexed raft RPCs (must be << raft-heartbeat-interval) (default 2ms)
      --quic-mux-pool int                                   stream pool size per peer for multiplexed raft RPCs (avoids HoL with raft pipelining) (default 4)
      --raft-addr string                                    Raft listen address for cluster communication (required in cluster mode)
      --raft-election-timeout duration                      per-group raft election timeout (must be >= 3 * heartbeat-interval). Higher = fewer spurious elections under load. (default 1s)
      --raft-heartbeat-interval duration                    per-group raft heartbeat interval. Lower = faster failure detection, higher CPU/network. Default 200ms balances detection latency with QUIC stream-open cost. (default 200ms)
      --raft-log-gc-interval duration                       how often Raft log GC runs (default 30s)
      --reshard-interval duration                           background EC reshard interval (always on; 0 resets to default 24h) (default 24h0m0s)
      --scrub-interval duration                             EC shard scrub interval (always on; 0 resets to default 24h) (default 24h0m0s)
      --scrub-orphan-age duration                           minimum filesystem mtime age before an orphan raw segment is eligible for sweep (default 5m0s)
      --segment-gc-retention duration                       grace period before unreferenced raw segment blobs are GC'd (default 24h0m0s)
      --shard-cache-size int                                EC shard cache capacity in bytes (0 disables) (default 1073741824)
      --shard-pack-threshold int                            pack cluster shards below this size into node-local append-only shard packs (0 = disabled, e.g. 65545) (default 65545)
      --strict-vlog-registry                                fatal on vlog registry smoke mismatch (e2e: true)
      --vlog-critical-ratio float                           vlog/disk ratio that fires critical (default 0.7)
      --vlog-eta-window duration                            ETA projection window for vlog warnings (default 30m0s)
      --vlog-poll-interval duration                         vlog watcher sampling cadence (default 1m0s)
      --vlog-recovery-window duration                       minimum time below warn ratio before transitioning to ok (default 5m0s)
      --vlog-smoke-defer duration                           delay before vlog registry startup smoke runs (default 1m0s)
      --vlog-warn-ratio float                               vlog/disk ratio that fires warn (transition-only) (default 0.4)
      --vlog-watch-enabled                                  enable BadgerDB vlog watcher (PR2) (default true)

Global Flags:
      --log-level string   log level: debug, info, warn, error (default "info")
